dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2193  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: DGKZ was enriched in postsynaptic density fractions.\nDGKZ was localized in in cell bodies, dendrites, and dendritic spines.\n\n26/01/2018 Pim\n- DGKZ interacts and colocalizes with PSD-95.. Experimental description: Materials and methods\nFractionation of rat brain lysates\nSubcellular fractions of rat brains (6 weeks) were prepared as described (Huttner et al, 1983).\nElectron microscopy\nTwo male Sprague-Dawley rats (280-300 g) were deeply anaesthetized with sodium pentobarbital (80 mg/kg, i.p.) and intracardially perfused with a mixture of 4% paraformaldehyde and 0.01% glutaraldehyde in phosphate buffer (PB, pH 7.4).\n\nHuttner WB, Schiebler W, Greengard P, De Camilli P (1983) Synapsin I (protein I), a nerve terminal-specific phosphoprotein. III. Its association with synaptic vesicles studied in a highly purified synaptic vesicle preparation. J Cell Biol 96: 1374-1388" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2193" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

